description.narrative: Mandated systems, mechanisms and processes for protection of girls, boys and women are organised/re-organised and further strengthened in priority cities, municipalities and barangays and contributes to reducing risk and strengthening resilience., which contributes to Child Protection And Emergencies, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By end of CP, improved and inclusive access to well-coordinated national and local child protection services in 10 LGU's supported by a functional public sector institutional framework focused on protective elements of Early Child Development (ECD), and promoting equity andsocial inclusion, in coordination with Social Protection and a broader Social Protection strategy.
